paragraphs.title: Train The ALS Model
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.ml.recommendation.ALS

val rank = 10 // this is k
val maxIterations = 5
val convergenceThreshold = 0.01

val als = new ALS()
  .setRank(rank)
  .setRegParam(convergenceThreshold)
  .setUserCol("userId")
  .setItemCol("itemId")
  .setRatingCol("rating")

val model = als.fit(itemRatingsDF)

paragraphs.title: Generate Personalized Recommendations For All Users
paragraphs.text:
model.setPredictionCol("confidence")
val recommendationsDF = model.transform(itemRatingsDF.select($"userId", $"itemId")).toDF("userId", "recommendedItemId", "confidence")

val enrichedRecommendationsDF = 
   recommendationsDF.join(itemsDF, $"itemId" === $"recommendedItemId")
   .select($"userId", $"recommendedItemId", $"title", $"tags", $"confidence")
   .sort($"userId", $"recommendedItemId", $"confidence" desc)
   
z.show(enrichedRecommendationsDF.select($"userId", $"recommendedItemId", $"title", $"confidence"))

paragraphs.title: userFactor Vector dot product ItemFactor vector
Convert ALS Item Factors Into K-Means Feature Vectors
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.mllib.linalg.Vectors
import org.apache.spark.sql.Row

val itemFeatureVectorsDF = model.itemFactors.map(row => (row.getInt(0), row.getSeq[Float](1)))
  .mapValues(row => Vectors.dense(row(2)))
  .toDF("id", "features")
  .as("itemFeatureVectors")
